  "text": "All the 13 known Finnish IOSCA families, with 42 healthy and 19 affected family members, were included in this study. Informed consent was obtained from all the families. Six families had two affected children, the rest only one affected child. The patients were diagnosed at the Children's Hospital of the University of Helsinki. The diagnosis was based on the following clinical symptoms: acute or subacute appearance of ataxia, athetosis, and the loss of deep tendon reflexes in a child with normal development until the age of 9 to 18 mo as well as deafness, ophthalmoplegia, optic atrophy, and sensory neuropathy, which subsequently developed during childhood years [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
